

RIDDLE



LOGIC PUZZLE

CHART THE PATH
A grid map with a bunch of town names or street names that the recipient has a relationship to. 
They are all laid out on the grid, The puzzle asks you to follow the path of four/five individuals
E.G. He took a left towards Manhattan, etc. Person B took a head towards the setting sun. 
In the end, each individual path spells out a letter. Together they spell out a number. E-I-G-H-T.


Harry
